stylometry: Transportation problems are when items are shipped from point A (origin) to point B (destination). The locations are called nodes. The arc is the pathway from one node to another and the flow is what is being sent across each node. Transshipment problems are when the destination then becomes and origin. For example, a manufacturer (origin 1) sends inventory over to walmart (destination 1). Walmart recieved an online order for this inventory so Walmart (origin 2) then ships it out to the customer (destination 2).
